Merge pull request #14 from roadrunner2/master

Ignore errors when closing file-descriptors.

Ignore errors when closing file-descriptors.

In particular, if one of these functions are called with closefds=true
shortly after a failed TCPSocket, the ObjectSpace iterator will find that
socket; but even called closed? on the socket will throw an error. Since
failing to close an fd is unlikely to be a serious issue, we just ignore
any errors.

Add Open4::pfork4 for executing arbitrary Ruby code

Like popen4, but instead of executing command line, call arbitrary Ruby
code in a child process via a lambda.

We must use lambda for passing the code, because the block argument of
pfork4 is reserved for controlling the pipes. This is analogous to
popen4.

pfork4 propagates any exception raised in the child process to the
parent process if pfork4 is called with a block. This makes error
handling in the parent process more natural than with checking child
process exit status (which would destroy all exception information too).
